description: Collecting the best-selling 5-issue miniseries! With the Guardians of the Universe back, the time has come to re-form the fabled Green Lantern Corps. While some familiar ring-wielders return to duty, others are recruited — and not everyone appreciates being drafted!
name: HC/TPB

description: Riverdale High’s star players, Archie and Moose, are out of the game! Can the cheerleaders rally “The Big Turnaround” in time to bring the boys back in play for the big game against Central!? Then the presence of cash, or lack thereof, presents a holiday dilemma for Archie in “Christmas Presence.”
name: The Big Turnaround!

description: As the demon king looms over the city, Joe has to decide between joining his fellow cat masters in battle or helping his ex save her current man from a dismal fate in an underground chalk shop. The final explosive issue—with a bonus comic-sized color poster inside!

The Darkest Tale of The Darkness Yet!

Just as the Brotherhood of The Darkness existed to serve the interests of The Darkness on Earth, another cult has existed in secret serving the needs of The Angelus on this world. Now armed with a legendary weapon crafted from the heart of a sun itself, a servant of the cult within Jackie’s inner circle moves to end the Estacado line once and for all.
name: The Apostate

description: The original miniseries based on the best-selling Capcom game comes to its dramatic conclusion! Holiday Sugarman goes one-on-one with the bio-weapon-enhanced Giesel while Mina Gere leads BSAA forces in a desperate attempt to stop Giesel's apocalyptic failsafe device. Don't miss the stunning finale!
name: Schafft Chaos Und Lasst Die Kriegshunde Los

description: Beaky Buzzard is famished. The good news is: Daffy Duck is on hand to help, and he's got the perfect meal. The bad news is: the meal is Bugs Bunny!
name: Looney Yule

description:
With one word - KIMOTA! - newspaper copy boy Micky Moran becomes the invincible, indestructible Marvelman! In 1954, MARVELMAN #25 began the saga of one of the most storied characters ever to emerge from the British comics market. Now, thrill to the adventures of Marvelman, Young Marvelman and Kid Marvelman as they take on enemy agents, mad scientists and more in this 'best of' series!

Reprints:

  • Marvelman #65
  • Marvelman #77
  • Young Marvelman #202
  • Marvelman Family #18
  • Marvelman Family #29

The chronicle of the Marvel Universe continues as the All-New Official Index to the Marvel Universe delves into the history of three of Marvel’s most enduring titles! Return with us to the Silver and Golden Ages as we continue our coverage of the Avengers (from AVENGERS #254), Thor (from THOR #358), and Captain America (from both CAPTAIN AMERICA #304 and 1941’s CAPTAIN AMERICA COMICS #29). Watch the Marvel universe’s history unfold month by month as each issue provides synopses for dozens of individual comics, including back-up strips, introducing the characters, teams, places and equipment that appeared within, providing vital information about first appearances, where they last showed up and where they appeared next!

volume.name: Avengers, Thor & Captain America: Official Index to the Marvel Universe

description: “Fishnapped!” Dory is taken from the reef by a mysterious group and only her friends can save her. Join Marlin, Nemo and Gill as they embark on a quest to save Dory from her elusive captors. And what happens next will shock all the fish in the sea! The biggest selling DVD of all time comes to comics in a brand-new adventure that FINDING NEMO fans will be talking about for ages.
name: Finding Nemo: Losing Dory
The legend of the Kohta Falaya: Johnny Returns

description: Bo reminisces on her first discovery of her ability, and chooses how to use it.
name: Chapter Three - Futakuchi-onna

volume.name: Lost Girl: The Interactive Motion Comic

description: Dyson and Hale continue their investigation, putting themselves in jeopardy.
name: Chapter Four - Dead Leads

description: It features 4 different comic stories. The second story features Rulah The Jungle Goddess relettered as Kolah. The story is called "Desperate Peril!" aka "The Runaway Balloon" initially included in Rulah - Jungle Goddess #27.
